
Formulae

m=100000007

1 (a+b)%m =((a%m) + (b%m))%m
2 (a*b)%m =((a%m)*(b%m))%m
3 (a-b)%m =((a%m) - (b%m)+m)%m
4 (a/b)%m =((a%m)*(b^-1)%m)%m  => (a/b) ==> (a*1/b)

10^9+7
---> close to max integer range
---> being a prime, we can calculate multiplicative inverse from 1 to m


