Multiplicative Inverse
4 (a/b)%m =((a%m)*(b^-1)%m)%m  => (a/b) ==> (a*1/b)

we know x*1/x=1
given x & m, calculate x^-1 , assume y=x^-1
y is inverse mod of x when  (x*y)%m=1

y wont exists always like there is no inverse modulo of 0
0*(1/0) ccant be 1
1/0 --> undefined

y exists only if following conditions holds
1) gcd(x,m)=1 i.e they are co primes
2) value of y lies in between [1,m-1]


FERMATS Little Theorem

If p is prime & a%p!=0

a^(p-1)%p=1

==>>
a^(p-1) mod p=1 mod p
multiplying a^-1 on both

a^(p-2) mod p=a^-1 mod p
then (a^-1)%p=(a^(p-2))%p



